Package: sharefs
Title: Fast Filesystem Operations for Network Shares
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Or", "Gadish", email = "orgadish@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Description: Batched alternatives to base R's file listing, metadata, and
    copy functions, built specifically for reading files off an SMB/CIFS
    network share (a mapped network drive or UNC path) on Windows, where
    each individual file operation -- listing a directory, 'stat()'-ing a
    file, copying a file -- pays a full network round trip. 'sharefs' uses
    a single 'PowerShell' 'Get-ChildItem' call to list a directory
    together with file metadata, and 'robocopy' to stage files locally,
    instead of one call per file. There is no cross-platform speedup to
    offer -- 'fs' already covers the general case well -- so this package
    is Windows-only rather than pretending otherwise; see the 'fs'
    package for the same operations everywhere else.
